The Osun State Governorship Election Petitions Tribunal sitting in Abuja has declared as illegal the September 27, 2018 supplementary governorship election held in seven polling units as illegal. The tribunal held that the supplementary election was a product of an illegal cancellation of the results in the seven polling units during the September 22, 2018 main election. It ruled that the Returning Officer who cancelled the results had no power to do so. The Peoples Democratic Party and its governorship candidate, Ademola Adeleke, in the election had filed the petition urging the tribunal to declare that Adeleke polled the highest lawful votes and be declared the winner. Osun State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) yesterday filed a petition before election petition tribunal to challenge victory of the governorship candidate of the All Progressive Congress (APC), Mr. Gboyega Oyetola.   Oyetola was declared winner of the 22nd September, 2018 governorship election in the state by the… In “News” TEMITOPE OGUNBANKE reports on major winners and losers of the Osun State governorship election       The just-concluded Osun State governorship election was a keenly-contested poll in the history of the state. Despite being described as a free, fair and violence-free, the September 22 poll was not decided at… In “Politics” The Independent National Electoral Commission’s (INEC’s) declaration of last Saturday’s governorship election in Osun State as inconclusive has brought to the fore, the bug of inconclusive polls that ushered in the current management of the nation’s electoral umpire, FELIX NWANERI reports   Has the Prof. Mahmood Yakubu-led management of the… In “Politics”